pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [ ] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the new behavior?
Adds a new TA grading interface (beta). 

How to test and review this new interface.
There is a new button added in the TA navigation bar from where you can access this interface.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/84874447-83175880-b07c-11ea-9899-2ef6ee7a2159.png)

What's new in this interface?
- Fixes the sidebar menu scroll [issue](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/issues/4194) as earlier it was not possible to pick the menu items which were offscreen. 
- Scraps out the earlier floating panel layout as they were hard to manage and less acessible. 
- A fixed structure is added (aka single-panel-mode) where a single panel is shown at a time taking all the available space.
- Each panel can be toggled with the help of buttons given inside the new panel-header-box which corresponds to one of these panels OR by just pressing the corresponding hotkey which can be configured on-site.
- Introduces a two-panel-mode for power-users of this interface, where two panels can be opened side-by-side. A drag-bar is provided in between these two panels which can be used to resize and adjust the width of panels as per the user's choice.
- Introduces full-left-column-mode where left column of the two-panel-mode takes the complete height of its container and the navigation-bar + panels-header-box is shifted to the right side of the layout. And this is again resizeable just as the normal two-panel-mode.
- Also there is a button provided in the navigation bar to exchange the positions of currently opened panels i.e panel opened in left goes to right and right one goes to left. 
- Adds another power-user feature i.e the full-screen-mode or focus-mode in which the grading interface goes full screen and there is no side-bar or submitty top navigation bar, and this works for both single and two-panel-mode.
 
### Screenshots

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/86264074-f7dcad80-bbb9-11ea-9191-cd16312d08d3.png)


### Other information?
~This interface doesnot know about all panels that are present for a certain gradeable, and might be missing some key panels (or displaying extra panel) like peer-grading panel or discussion panel, and I'm working on that.~ DONE

pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Currently clicking on the panel-selector button changes the ta-grading layout serially i.e single panel -> two-panel -> three-panel. And for turning the left column in 'full-left-column' mode there is an additional button on the toolbar.

### What is the new behavior?

Adds panel-selector modal for switching between all the available ta-grading layout modes. This modal can be accessed from the same panel-selector button which is used currently. Also this removes the 'full-left-col' button from the toolbar and provides the option for same from the modal itself.

![Group 13358](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/90412651-46c89e80-e0a5-11ea-9557-69b29fe3a49f.png)


### Other information?
Should be merged only after the [PR](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/pull/5759) which adds third panel in the TA-grading page.

pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Currently, the new TA grading interface only supports a maximum of two panels to be shown.

### What is the new behavior?
Introduce the third panel in the ta-grading interface. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/89006485-c7924700-d2fe-11ea-8fca-8194360bce47.png)


### Steps to Use/this new panel
1. Navigate to the ta-grading page
2. Click on the `tags` icon in the panel-header to enter new interface
3. Click on columns (panels) icon to switch between all the panel mode 

### Other information?
If you previously have opened this new TA grading interface you will need to clear out your localstorage... or paste this `localstorage.clear()` in your JS console.

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Currently, there is no solution /TA notes panel

### What is the new behavior?
Partially closes the issue #5648 
In this PR "Solution/Ta notes" panel is added and this lets instructors use shared notes and points for each of the rubric-components. 
- Lets you add solutions and notes which can be used as a reference by other instructors grading students
- Shows the last edit and the name of the author
- Each rubric component is connected to a corresponding solution box.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/89914162-877b7000-dbec-11ea-991d-5a4f2aa6277a.png)


### Other information?

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior? 
Currently, there is no Solution / TA notes panel on the TA-grading page.

### What is the new behavior?
Incremental PR to solve issue #5648 
The "Solution/Ta notes" panel will be added by the PR #5801. This PR adds following features in the Solution/Ta notes panel.
 - [x] For notebook gradeables, provide an option to attach rubric-components with the item-pool.
 - [x] Provides only those itempool options where randomization of items (questions) is possible.
 - [x]  Solution Panel is linked with the itempool options if the rubric-component supports itempool.
 - [x] While grading a student, instructor only see solutions/notes which are representing the selected item for the current student from the itempool.
 Additionally, this PR fixes the issue of hotkeys in the TA-grading page and also adds hotkeys for the recently added "Notebook" panel (KeyN) and for the "Solution/TA-notes" panel (KeyT)

### Other information?
To be merged only after the PR #5801

pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Currently, if there are multiple items that are available in `from_pool`, hashing is done to pick one of these questions.
Also, there is an unhandled `undefined key error` case ( for 'type' ) which is popping out on some gradeable.

### What is the new behavior?
Closes #5647 
Fixes undefined index error. 
Adds support for optional field `user_item_map`.  This object contains a mapping of usernames to the index of items present in the `from_pool` array. 
```
          "user_item_map": {
                "<username_0> : <index_0>,
                "<username_1> : <index_1>....
              },
```
Users in this mapping will only be shown item corresponding to the mentioned index next to their username and no hash-based randomization will be done for them.
These ensure instructors can proofread all the question before exam... see #5647 for more info

### Other information?
Added this key in item_pool_random gradeable config.json for testing :)

* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Currently, all the Plagiarism page code is written in PlagiarismView.php and there are no corresponding twig files for these pages. So after refactoring this all, I have added a couple of twig files that store all the code for plagiarism main page, add/edit config page, plagiarism result page, which are then rendered by the plagiarismView.php much like the rest of the codebase. 
Also, these pages are made compatible across different sized screens.

pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the new behavior?
Adds an option to toggle full-screen mode and resize the width of columns containing plagiarism files in results page. 

### How to test?
Currently, there are only a few gradeables for which the plagiarism detector gives some results or show matches.
On the new configuration page choose `Autograder hidden and extra credits (C++ hidden tests)` as gradeable and `plain text` as `language`.

### Screenshots 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/86257850-01621780-bbb2-11ea-83e4-1d9f007b0e69.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/86258100-569e2900-bbb2-11ea-93e0-471b2a7e0ca7.png)


### Other information?
This PR is based on [refactor and mobile view of plagiarism PR](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/pull/5516)

pr_title: [Feature:Instructor-UI] Add an open date for grade inquiry
pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is current behavior?
Currently if the gradeable is enabled with grade inquiry, students can start making the grade inquiries as soon as the grades are released. This leads to students making frivolous grade inquiries without even reading about the solutions. 

### What is the current behavior?
Closes #4506 
With the introduction of opening date for the grade inquiry, instructors can set some offset between the grade released and grade inquiry date. Students will use this time to read and cross-check their solutions first and then come up with better grade inquiries.
Also, clear indications are provided to the students for the grade inquiries whether the grade inquiry is yet to be started , whats the due date and when did it end
![Screenshot 2020-07-03 at 8 23 19 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/86494420-f8697580-bd6c-11ea-94e3-421291d005a8.png)
![Screenshot 2020-07-03 at 8 21 05 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/86494417-f69fb200-bd6c-11ea-9812-7cff8eadc986.png)
![Screenshot 2020-07-03 at 8 36 35 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/86494422-f99aa280-bd6c-11ea-8527-c6ddb2159659.png)

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [x] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [x] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Currently, user profile info and the courses in which s/he is enrolled are shown on the home page.

### What is the new behavior?
Closes #5515 

Adds a separate space for the user profile information where they can view and update their various information (all Ajaxified, no page reloads!) like the basic info, profile photo, time-zone, and theme to use. Also, a separate page has been added to access all the archived and current courses in which they have participated in any form (student, instructor, or any type of grader). These pages can be accessed via the new menu options provided in the side navigation bar. 

Also, a single time-zone drop-down list is added with the UTC offset value attached to it. This list is sorted in increasing order wrt UTC offset values to let users find the best-suited time-zone quickly. (changes requested by @MasterOdin in this [comment](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/pull/5400#issuecomment-633136302).) 
 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/87671342-1d94b580-c769-11ea-93a7-71831fdb68d1.png)

### Other information?
~Might need to bring some more changes in the home page.
My courses page is WIP~

pr_title: [Feature: Instructor UI] XLSX/CSV Grader and Student Upload Need Better Error Messages
pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
At present, a failed CSV or XLSX upload to add new students or graders only specifies which row an error occurs on. This does not give a clear indication of what went wrong and leaves the user confused. 
Also, XLSX file upload is broken. 

### What is the new behavior?
Closes #3629 #5588 
Now an errored CSV/XLSX document gives a clear error message along with the formating suggestions for the columns in which errors occurred. This helps users to debug that error easily. Also, the XLSX file upload issue is fixed now.

pr_title: [Feature: Forum] Full page forum to browse threads
pr_body:
### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Partially closes [#5327](https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/issues/4795) 

### What is the new behavior?
Full page forum ( or main/entry page for the forum) can be accessed on the route `/courses/<semester>/<course>/forum`. This page has been added to let users browse all the threads.  Users can search threads, apply filters on the list of threads, Edit, delete threads, and create threads from this page. 

![Screenshot 2020-08-17 at 10 01 49 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/90472047-8203b580-e117-11ea-8c98-7d772345f952.png)


### Other information?
It doesn't add the following point from  PR and can be done in separate PR if needed 
1. #of posts, # of unread posts, # of participants
2. contains image attachments
3. whether the top post is edited

Currently, there is a spacing bug in the action buttons (browser is adding some DOM changes by itself)

Closes #6269

### What is the new behavior?

- [ ] Make Submitty installable on all the major platform as an app (PWA)
- [ ] Enable Push notification (in addition to all the onsite-notification which have currently) to keep students and instructors informed with latest development across all the courses.

### Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements:

* [x] The PR title and message follows our [guidelines](https://submitty.org/developer/how_to_contribute)
* [ ] Tests for the changes have been added/updated (if possible)
* [ ] Documentation has been updated/added if relevant

### What is the current behavior?
Next/prev assigned ungraded (double arrow) buttons generate error when
-  grading is completed, or 
-  you have already graded all the assigned students to you, or
-  you try to jump off the assigned student list (accessing prev assigned ungraded student from the very first assigned student or accessing the next student from the last one). 

### What is the new behavior?
Fixes #5662 
Does not throw an error (frog) and instead shows the popup that the asked student is not found.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48342617/87083621-d23c4d80-c224-11ea-981e-12b7285b940c.png)
